  "text": "We should point out that ICNet [CITATION_1] employs the Cascade Feature Fusion (CFF) module to combine the cascade features from the different resolution inputs. CFF respectively performs the atrous convolution with BN and the projection convolution with BN for two inputs and then concatenates the outputs from the two convolutions. In contrast, FFN concatenates the inputs from different branches, and then performs the atrous convolution and projection convolution in a cascaded way. This is mainly because that the number of channels for two inputs from the semantic branch and the spatial branch is different. Therefore, we cannot directly use the CFF module in FFN.",
